Sports Writers Association of Nigeria (SWAN) President Honour Sirawoo has called on media practitioners to shun forces that are set forth to foster disunity within the media fraternity and Nigeria at large. Sirawoo made the  clarion  call at the end of  the quarters finals matches of the on-going SWAN Kano chapter inter media cup holding  at the Kano Pillars Stadium. Sirawoo, who commended  SWAN Kano  state chapter for portraying   the bond among media practitioner could enjoy through sports, further  advocates for a firm commitment and unity in the media fraternity.   Sanwo Olu-leads government delegation to AFCON     Fresh rebels threat at Eagles’ venue in Garoua     Egypt also fears  Nigeria  says Musa   Represented by the Vice President, SWAN North West Lurwanu Idris Malikawa, Sirawoo  said: “ Unity is our strength, this competition has served as an indicator of the strength in our  muscle, which  we possess as a union. “We must not allow our focus to be deviated from the motive and objectives set forth by the founding fathers of our great association. - Advertisement - “ As media practitioners, we are the  bearers of the torch of unity and progress, along  with the task to make sure those for running national affairs  are made to remain steadfast and responsible ,  dedicated and accountable  to the task and role in their duty of  nation building,” he noted inter alia.